OL,3,CCautious optimism for Nissan in
OL,4,CSunderland despite 20,000 global job
OL,5,Closses
OL,7,FNissan has confirmed it will shut
OL,8,Fseven factories and cut 20,000 jobs
OL,9,Fglobally in a bid to slash costs.
OL,10,FThere is no word yet as to where those
OL,11,Fcuts will fall yet but in a worldwide
OL,12,Fpress conference, the CEO confirmed
OL,13,Fmore cars will be made at the Wearside
OL,14,Ffactory.
OL,16,FThe Japanese car maker has said it
OL,17,Fwill cut 11,000 more jobs than
OL,18,Foriginally planned, having announced
OL,19,Fin November that it would axe 9,000
OL,20,Froles in a restructuring.
